It amazes me that focus pullers like Chloe can make every single shot tack sharp with no viewfinder using only a knowledge of maths and lens/light physics. It's crazy that she can look at a subject 10m away and know that the lens is at 100mm and know on a moment by moment basis the exact number to turn the dial to on the fly to get a perfectly crisp shot. There's zero room for error with focus pulling as it's one of the only things that can't be fixed in post-production. mad respect ğŸ™ŒğŸ»
